args:
With the sun setting over the plains, the party
decides to call it a day. During the night watch,
Mascula chats with Luca about the pleasures of
a meal with friends, making him even more
aware of the lonely existence he leads.
Looks like the sun's about to set.\nLet's rest here for the night.

I'm so hungry I could eat a bearcowken!
That's a chicken stuffed into a cow
stuffed into a bear, by the way.
Oh man, I'm drooling... Mmrrrggh...
I don't think I have access to all of those\ningredients, but I will see what I can do.
Hey, yeah. Do you even eat, Mascula?
Yes. We androids can replenish our energy\nwith organic food.

However, we are able to convert a wider
range of substances into energy than
people can. For example, the soil floor
of the surrounding area would suffice.
Well, that sounds handy! Still, ya might\nas well eat with us instead of munchin'\non dirt or whatever.
Huh? Did I say somethin' weird?

No, it's just that food shortages
were common on battlefields of old,
so we generally avoided eating the
same things as people.
Sounds like you had a pretty rough\ntime of it back in the day.
We were merely making\nthe pragmatic choice.
It is inefficient for us to consume the food\nof people when we have other options.
Ha! That sounds like someone who's\nnever shared a good meal with friends!\nAin't nothin' more delicious than that!
If you're with us, you're with us.\nAnd that means we eat together!
I don't know what to say...
Cleo, yer the damn BEST!\nI don't eat this well at an inn,\nmuch less on a battlefield!
Yeah, we're crazy lucky to have you\ntraveling with us, girl!

Look, sometimes even a cold-hearted
merc like me needs to express what's
in his heart—and right now, my heart
is stuffed full'a tasty chow!
Ranzal's right! ...Which is SUPER weird.\nBut yeah, you always need to take the\ntime to tell people stuff like that.
Ah. I think I see what is happening here.

While I am delighted to hear such lavish
praise, I fear no amount of sweet talk will
produce additional helpings; what you
see in front of you is all we have.
Cold! ICE cold! Ya WOUND me, Cleo!\nHere I am just tryin' to tell ya how great\nya are, and ya gotta go and do me dirty!
Oh? Well, in that case, perhaps I will\ngive this extra serving to someone el—
On the OTHER hand, a nice compliment\nlike that probably deserves a little\nsomethin' sweet, yeah?
What's up, Mascula? You seem spacey.
My apologies if the meal is not to your\nliking. I have little experience preparing\nfood for your kind.
No, it's fine. Or rather...we androids\nin fact lack the ability to ＂taste.＂
Wait, so everything just tastes like a big\npile of bland cardboard mush? Duuuuude!
Oh, man. Maybe I shouldn't have pushed\nthis whole eating thing on you, then.
No, it was a good idea.
In fact, you have made me reconsider the\nconcept of replenishing energy stores.
You mentioned the deliciousness of\na meal taken with friends, yes?
And I am finding this meal enjoyable.\nI even feel like I'm beginning to\nunderstand the concept of ＂taste.＂
I think what I'm feeling right now is the\n＂deliciousness＂ that you spoke of earlier.
Thank you, everyone. This is the most\nenjoyable time I've ever spent.
Oh, nothin'. Just thought I'd come\nhang with ya for a bit.
Oh? If you're concerned about the watch,\nall is well. There's no sign of enemies in\nthe area.
I can cover a wide area by myself while\nengaged in search mode. You should\ntake this opportunity to rest.
Fatigue is a constant problem for organics\nlike yourself as I understand it.
Well, sure, we all gotta sleep.\nBut YOU need to rest, too.
Just because ya don't need to sleep\ndoesn't mean ya don't need REST.
No one can keep goin' a million miles an\nhour, no matter how awesome they are.\nSo get some rest, yeah?
But, as I lack the functionality for sleep,\nI don't know how to engage in ＂rest.＂
In that case, how 'bout you and me\njust hang and chew the fat for a bit.

Yeah! Chat! Talk! Spill the beans!
Night watch is boring as hell when
there ain't an enemy tryin' to kill ya.
I always find it lonely, personally.
Lonely... Yes, I see. That's what it was.
From time to time, I've been assaulted\nby a curious feeling. Like something's\nmissing. Like I've forgotten something...
I believe this feeling was loneliness.
But hey, you're gonna be fine now,\n'cause ya got ME!
Ain't no cure for loneliness like\nwhoopin' it up with a buddy!
A buddy. You mean a friend, yes?\nThen you are...my friend?
R-right!\nI have a friend... I'm not lonely anymore...
